'''The Mythopoeic Literature Society of Australia''', was a [[Tolkien Societies|Tolkien society]] and mythical literature society in Australia. This society was presumably an Australian counterpart of the US based [[Mythopoeic Society]].

==History==
As of [[2024]], only scattered references to this society can be found.<ref>http://arts.monash.edu.au/ecps/assets/docs/cv-peter-groves.pdf (accessed 05-12-2011)</ref> It is therefore assumed that this society is now defunct. This society appears to have been active from the mid 1980s through the early 1990s.

==Publications==
This society published:
* [[1986]]: ''The Nameless Wood: Victorian Fantasists, their Achievement, their Influence'': Proceedings of the Second Annual Conference of the Inner Ring, the Mythopoeic Literature Society of Australia, [July] 1986, University of New England, Armidale, N.S.W.<ref>http://books.google.com/books/about/The_nameless_wood.html?id=kI-4OQAACAAJ (accessed 05-12-2011)</ref>
